7.9 Banks and non-banks shall be permitted to load / reload PPIs through their authorised outlets or through their authorised / designated agents subject to following conditions:-
a) Having a Board approved policy clearly laying down the framework for engaging
agents;

(ii) PPIs upto Rs.10,000/- (with no cash loading facility)
a) Banks and non-banks shall be permitted to issue such PPIs after obtaining minimum
details of the PPI holder;

Specific categories of PPIs

Banks and non-banks shall not issue PPIs of any other category except as permitted under the following categories:

10.1 Gift PPIs a) Maximum value of each such prepaid gift instrument shall not exceed Rs.10,000/-;

16.10 PPI issuer shall also be guided by the following DPSS circulars:
a) Harmonisation of Turn Around Time (TAT) and customer compensation for failed
transactions using authorised Payment Systems issued vide DPSS circular DPSS.CO.PD No.629/02.01.014/2019-20 dated September 20, 2019 (as amended from time to time);
